  "texts": [
    "These capabilities not only improve trust and accountability but also accelerate model validation by domain experts such as chemists and sensory scientists.",
    "Large language models (LLMs), while primarily developed for text, have shown strong potential in sensory domains through their ability to integrate knowledge across disciplines (Zhang et al. 2025).",
    "Fine-tuned on molecular databases, sensory ontologies, and food science literature, LLMs can assist in flavor pairing, molecular property prediction, and naturallanguage-driven formulation queries.",
    "For example, an LLM might recommend compatible ingredients based on target taste descriptors, or suggest molecular scaffolds with similar hedonic profiles.",
    "This convergence of language and chemistry enables a new paradigm for human-AI collaboration in ideation, discovery, and education within sensory science."
  ],
